{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"How a single Swift type becomes a world the engine can run."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/AnatomyOfAGame","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"article","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A Gnusto game is one type conforming to "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Game","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". That one type carries everything: the rooms and things, where they start, and the rules that govern them. This article covers the model underneath — how the engine finds your declarations, how one value is both a declaration and a live reference, and how the immutable world is kept separate from the state that changes as the player plays."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Once that model is clear, the rest of Gnusto follows from it.","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Declarations-are-stored-properties","text":"Declarations are stored properties"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Rooms, things, and custom state are declared as ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"stored properties","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" of the game type:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct OperaHouse: Game {","    let foyer = Location { name(\"Foyer of the Opera House\") }","    let bar   = Location { name(\"Foyer Bar\"); dark }","    let cloak = Item { name(\"velvet cloak\"); wearable }","    @Global var disturbances = 0","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you construct the world with "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameWorld\/init(game:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", the engine’s bootstrap reflects over the game value with "},{"code":"Mirror","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and collects every ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Location","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", and ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Global","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":". It names each entity after the property it was stored in: ","type":"text"},{"code":"foyer","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" becomes ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/EntityID","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"foyer\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"cloak","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" becomes ","type":"text"},{"code":"\"cloak\"","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", and so on. You never write these IDs by hand — the property name ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"is","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" the name.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is why declarations must live in the type’s main body, not an extension: Swift only allows stored properties there, and the Mirror only sees stored properties. (When even the declarations need to span files or ship separately, that is what a "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" bundle is for — see "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":".)"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"One value, two roles","level":2,"anchor":"One-value-two-roles"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A declaration and a live reference are the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"same value","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let cloak = Item { name(\"velvet cloak\"); wearable }   \/\/ the declaration","","\/\/ …later, inside a rule body:","cloak.after(.take) {","    if cloak.isWorn { … }        \/\/ the live reference — reads current state","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"cloak","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is an ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item"},{"text":" value. Written in the game body it ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"declares"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" the cloak. Used in a rule it ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"reads and writes the live cloak’s state"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":": ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item\/isWorn"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item\/isHeld"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item\/name"},{"text":", and so on all consult the current turn.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This works because each ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Location","isActive":true},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" mints a private identity token when it is created. The token — not the struct’s contents — is the entity’s identity, and it survives copying. Two items are equal when they share a token ("},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item\/==(_:_:)"},{"type":"text","text":"). Inside a turn, the token resolves to the entity’s "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/EntityID"},{"type":"text","text":" and then to its state; outside a turn there is no state to read, so a live property access traps with an explanation rather than returning a meaningless value."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"References are always compile-checked. "},{"code":"cloak.after(.take)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"hook.holds(cloak)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"foyer.north(bar)"},{"type":"text","text":" — every one is ordinary property access, so renaming a room or deleting an item breaks the build instead of the running game."}]},{"level":2,"text":"The parts of the `Game` protocol","type":"heading","anchor":"The-parts-of-the-Game-protocol"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Game"},{"text":" gathers a handful of members, most with defaults so a small game declares only what it needs:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"title"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"intro","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"tagline"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"maxScore"},{"text":" — the banner and scoring metadata.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"text":" — geography and initial placement, as a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/WorldMap","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":". Read once at startup to build the initial state.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"rules","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — all game logic, as a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Rules","type":"reference"},{"text":" value. Defaults to empty.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"verbs"},{"type":"text","text":" — player-typeable verbs this game adds, as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"[SyntaxRule]"},{"type":"text","text":". Defaults to empty. See "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/AddingCustomVerbs","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"content","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — content bundles the game composes itself from, as ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContents","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":". Defaults to empty. See ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The protocol extension also hands every game three ambient references usable as bare identifiers inside "},{"code":"map","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"text":" blocks:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"player","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Player","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", for its location, score, and inventory."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"world","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/World","type":"reference"},{"text":", for rules that apply everywhere (like daemons).","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"command"},{"text":" — the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Command","isActive":true},{"text":" currently being performed, inside a rule body.","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"text":"The `map` block","anchor":"The-map-block","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"map","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is a result-builder property that yields a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/WorldMap","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" — a flat list of "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/MapEntry","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" statements: exits, blocked exits, initial item placements, and the player’s start.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["var map: WorldMap {","    foyer.south(bar)                 \/\/ an exit","    foyer.north(blocked: \"Not yet.\") \/\/ a blocked exit with a refusal message","    bar.north(foyer)","","    player.starts(in: foyer)         \/\/ where the player begins","    cloak.startsWorn                 \/\/ where each thing begins","    hook.starts(in: cloakroom)","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Exits are directional and one-way: ","type":"text"},{"code":"foyer.south(bar)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" does not imply ","type":"text"},{"code":"bar.north(foyer)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Declaring both is deliberate, so asymmetric maps (a chute, a one-way door) need no special case. Because ","type":"text"},{"code":"map","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is a builder, you can split it across files and compose it from sub-maps — see ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/SplittingAGameAcrossFiles","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Immutable definition, mutable state","type":"heading","anchor":"Immutable-definition-mutable-state","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Internally, the engine keeps two things strictly apart:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"definition"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is everything that never changes during play: names, descriptions, exits, rules, and the parser’s vocabulary. It is built once, from your declarations, at startup."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"state"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is everything that "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"does"}]},{"type":"text","text":" change: where each item is, what is lit, the score, the turn count, which things have been touched, and your "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Global","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" values."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The entire mutable state is a single ","type":"text"},{"code":"Codable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" value. That is a deliberate design choice: because all change funnels through one value, a turn’s mutations can be committed atomically at its end (see ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/TheTurnPipeline","type":"reference"},{"text":"), and save\/restore becomes a serialization call rather than a feature bolted across the codebase.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you write "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cloak.isWorn"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"player.score += 1"},{"type":"text","text":" in a rule, you are reading and writing that one state value through the entity’s token — never touching the definition, and never seeing another turn’s half-finished changes."}]},{"text":"See also","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"See-also"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GettingStarted","type":"reference","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/TheTurnPipeline"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/WritingRules","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"Gnusto"}],"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","title":"Anatomy of a Game"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gnusto\/anatomyofagame"]}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Essentials","title":"Essentials","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/TheTurnPipeline"]}],"references":{"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GameContent":{"abstract":[{"text":"A self-contained slice of a game’s world: its own rooms, items, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Global"},{"text":" state, plus the geography, rules, and verbs that go with them.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContent","title":"GameContent","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GameContent","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GameContent"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gamecontent","type":"topic"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Item/==(_:_:)":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item\/==(_:_:)","title":"==(_:_:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"=="},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:6Gnusto4ItemV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Item"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:6Gnusto4ItemV","text":"Item","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/item\/==(_:_:)","abstract":[{"text":"Two items are equal when they share the same declaration identity.","type":"text"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto":{"role":"collection","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto","type":"topic","title":"Gnusto","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A Swift engine for writing parser-driven interactive fiction — text adventures in the tradition of Zork and Infocom’s ZIL."}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GettingStarted":{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Build and run your first text adventure, one piece at a time."}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gettingstarted","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GettingStarted","title":"Getting Started with Gnusto"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GameWorld/init(game:)":{"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gameworld\/init(game:)","title":"init(game:)","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameWorld\/init(game:)","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"convenience"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"init"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"game"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:6Gnusto4GameP","text":"Game"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Builds the world from a game definition, validating it up front."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The random stream is seeded fresh each run; use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"init(game:seed:)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to replay a specific one."}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/AddingCustomVerbs":{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"Teach the parser words the built-in table doesn’t know.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/addingcustomverbs","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/AddingCustomVerbs","title":"Adding Custom Verbs"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Item":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Item"}],"role":"symbol","title":"Item","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Item"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/item","abstract":[{"text":"A thing in the world.","type":"text"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Game":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Game"}],"role":"symbol","title":"Game","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Game","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Game"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/game","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A complete game: declarations, geography, and rules."}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Item/name":{"title":"name","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item\/name","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The item’s display name."}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/item\/name","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"name"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/World":{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Rules that apply everywhere, declared through the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"world"},{"text":" identifier in a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"text":" block:","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"World","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"World","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/world","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/World","title":"World"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/GameContents":{"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GameContents","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"The collected content bundles a game declares, in declaration order.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/GameContents","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"GameContents"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/gamecontents","title":"GameContents","type":"topic","role":"symbol"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Player":{"title":"Player","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The player character, available as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"player"},{"type":"text","text":" inside any computed property"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Game"},{"type":"text","text":" type."}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Player","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Player","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/player","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Player","kind":"symbol"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/EntityID":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"EntityID"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A stable, human-readable entity name derived from the Swift property label"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at registration time ("},{"code":"let bar = Location { … }","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" → "},{"code":"EntityID(\"bar\")","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":")."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/EntityID","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"EntityID"}],"title":"EntityID","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/entityid","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"symbol"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Command":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A parsed player command, available inside rule bodies as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"command"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"topic","title":"Command","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Command","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Command","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/command","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Command"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/SplittingAGameAcrossFiles":{"role":"article","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/SplittingAGameAcrossFiles","type":"topic","title":"Splitting a Game Across Files","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/splittingagameacrossfiles","abstract":[{"text":"Keep a large game readable by composing its map and rules from per-region helpers.","type":"text"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/WorldMap":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/WorldMap","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The geography and initial placements of a game, declared in one block:"}],"title":"WorldMap","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"WorldMap","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"WorldMap"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/worldmap","type":"topic"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Item/isWorn":{"role":"symbol","title":"isWorn","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item\/isWorn","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"isWorn"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/item\/isworn","abstract":[{"text":"True if the player is wearing the item.","type":"text"}]},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/MapEntry":{"title":"MapEntry","abstract":[{"text":"One statement in a ","type":"text"},{"code":"map","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" block: an exit, a blocked exit, an initial item","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"placement, or the player’s starting location.","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MapEntry"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MapEntry"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/mapentry","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/MapEntry","kind":"symbol"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/WritingRules":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Attach game logic to items, locations, and the world."}],"type":"topic","title":"Writing Rules","kind":"article","role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/writingrules","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/WritingRules"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/TheTurnPipeline":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"What happens between the player pressing Return and the next prompt."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/TheTurnPipeline","title":"The Turn Pipeline","kind":"article","role":"article","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/theturnpipeline","type":"topic"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Item/isHeld":{"fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"isHeld","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"True if the player is carrying the item (including worn items)."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Item\/isHeld","title":"isHeld","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/item\/isheld","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"symbol"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Rules":{"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Rules","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The collected rules of a game, declared in one "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"rules"},{"type":"text","text":" block. Large games"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"compose: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"var rules: Rules { cloakRules; barRules }"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Rules","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Rules","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"Rules","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/rules","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","role":"symbol"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/ContentBundles":{"abstract":[{"text":"Give a region its own declarations — its own type, and even its own package.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/ContentBundles","title":"Content Bundles","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/contentbundles","type":"topic","role":"article"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Global":{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Custom game state with the same ergonomics as built-in state:","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Global"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Global"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/global","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Global","title":"Global"},"doc://Gnusto/documentation/Gnusto/Location":{"title":"Location","abstract":[{"text":"A place in the world.","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Location"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Location","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gnusto\/location","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/Gnusto\/documentation\/Gnusto\/Location","kind":"symbol"}}}